All port cities have this darkness to them. Lenin's family came from Astrakhan which is still called "India's gateway to Russia", they had Persian classes in the high school. Kazan's university was famous for "mysticism" and religious obscurantism, rectors held spiritual seances.

H. P. Lovecraft captures it in "The Shadow over Innsmouth" better than anyone in the context of the East Coast, but Russian port cities like Astrakhan and Kazan were the same way. There were Chinese minorities, Iranian communities, Swedenborgian Naval masonic lodges, astrologers.
